No more about conſcience.—But come, I'll put it to the trial, and here is the ordeal,
(takes out a purſe);
here is the general abſolution that ſalves all conſciences.—This opens and ſhuts the mouths of the moſt vociferous orators, blinds the eyes of the church, deafens the ears of magiſtrates, obliterates the judgment of the law, arreſts the arm of juſtice, and dries up the fountains of mercy. How feels your conſcience now?

Here, firrah;
(gives money.)
This can procure you every thing but that you want moſt, honeſty.
